I stopped evaluating models in isolation. I build what I call a workflow package: skill + prompt + context.

The skill defines what to do. The prompt defines how to instruct. The context defines what to know.

I run the same workflow package against each new model as it drops. Benchmark model + workflow together, not model alone. When I own the workflow package, every new model release becomes a simple swap-and-compare. That's only possible if the components are mine.
